headline: Intuit (INTU) Valuation Check After Strong Q1 Beat, AI Expansion and Mixed Small Business Outlook
summary: Intuit (INTU) just cleared a big checkpoint, topping its fiscal Q1 2026 guidance while doubling down on AI and still standing by its full year outlook, even with slightly softer SMB guidance. See our latest analysis for Intuit. Still, the stock has cooled a bit, with a modest year to date share price return of about 5 percent and a slightly negative one year total shareholder return, as investors weigh stellar AI driven execution against softer SMB guidance and ongoing insider selling, even...
